New Records: Ireland's first T-20 win over Pakistan.
Key Match Events: Craig Young took two crucial wickets in one over, dismissing Babar Azam and Azam Khan.
Andrew Balbirnie and Harry Tector put on a 75-run partnership.
Curtis Campher took a leg bye off the penultimate ball to seal the victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netizens reacted strongly to Pakistan's loss, with some calling it the worst Pakistan team in history.
Discussions on whether teams like Ireland and Netherlands should be part of mainstream cricket.
Suggestions to give the captaincy of Pakistan Cricket Team back to Shaheen Shah Afridi.
